# How to Split Text Between Two Words in Java

## Quick Reference

### 1. Extract Everything Between Two Words
```java
// Extract content between "START" and "END"
Pattern pattern = Pattern.compile("START(.*?)END", Pattern.DOTALL);
Matcher matcher = pattern.matcher(text);
while (matcher.find()) {
    String content = matcher.group(1).trim();
    results.add(content);
}
```

### 2. Split Starting at One Word, Ending at Another
```java
// Split at each "Outfit:" and stop at "Why:"
String[] blocks = text.split("(?=Outfit:)");
for (String block : blocks) {
    if (block.contains("Why:")) {
        String outfit = block.substring(0, block.indexOf("Why:")).trim();
        results.add(outfit);
    }
}
```

## Real Examples for Your Use Case

### Example 1: Extract Outfit Items Only (between "Outfit:" and "Why:")
```java
private java.util.List<String> parseOutfits(String suggestions) {
    java.util.List<String> results = new java.util.ArrayList<>();

    // Pattern to match: "Outfit:" ... anything ... "Why:"
    Pattern pattern = Pattern.compile("Outfit[^:]*:(.*?)Why:", Pattern.DOTALL);
    Matcher matcher = pattern.matcher(suggestions);

    while (matcher.find()) {
        String outfitItems = matcher.group(1).trim();
        results.add(outfitItems);
    }

    return results;
}
```

**Input:**
```
Outfit 1:
- Blue jeans
- White t-shirt
Why: Perfect for warm weather

Outfit 2:
- Black pants
- Red sweater
Why: Good for cold days
```

**Output:**
```
["- Blue jeans\n- White t-shirt", "- Black pants\n- Red sweater"]
```

### Example 2: Extract Individual Clothing Items (each line starting with "-")
```java
private java.util.List<String> parseOutfits(String suggestions) {
    java.util.List<String> results = new java.util.ArrayList<>();

    // Split by lines starting with "-"
    String[] lines = suggestions.split("\n");
    for (String line : lines) {
        if (line.trim().startsWith("-")) {
            String item = line.trim().substring(1).trim(); // Remove "-"
            results.add(item);
        }
    }

    return results;
}
```

**Output:**
```
["Blue jeans", "White t-shirt", "Black pants", "Red sweater"]
```

### Example 3: Get Complete Outfit Blocks (from "Outfit" to next "Outfit" or end)
```java
private java.util.List<String> parseOutfits(String suggestions) {
    java.util.List<String> results = new java.util.ArrayList<>();

    // Split at each "Outfit" keeping it in result
    String[] blocks = suggestions.split("(?=Outfit\\s*\\d*:?)");

    for (String block : blocks) {
        String trimmed = block.trim();
        if (!trimmed.isBlank() && trimmed.startsWith("Outfit")) {
            results.add(trimmed);
        }
    }

    return results;
}
```

**Output:**
```
[
  "Outfit 1:\n- Blue jeans\n- White t-shirt\nWhy: Perfect for warm weather",
  "Outfit 2:\n- Black pants\n- Red sweater\nWhy: Good for cold days"
]
```

## Regex Pattern Breakdown

### Basic Pattern: `START(.*?)END`
- `START` - Literal text to start from
- `(.*?)` - Capture group (what you want to extract)
  - `.` - Any character
  - `*?` - Zero or more times (non-greedy)
- `END` - Literal text to end at

### Common Modifiers:
- `Pattern.DOTALL` - Makes `.` match newlines too
- `Pattern.CASE_INSENSITIVE` - Ignore case
- `(?=...)` - Positive lookahead (doesn't consume text)
- `(?<=...)` - Positive lookbehind (look back)

## More Examples

### Split Between "Weather" and "Outfit"
```java
String[] parts = text.split("(?=Outfit)");
String weatherSection = parts[0];
// Rest are outfits
```

### Extract Just the "Why" Explanations
```java
Pattern pattern = Pattern.compile("Why:\\s*(.*?)(?=Outfit|$)", Pattern.DOTALL);
Matcher matcher = pattern.matcher(text);
while (matcher.find()) {
    String explanation = matcher.group(1).trim();
    results.add(explanation);
}
```

### Extract Clothing Items as List Per Outfit
```java
Pattern outfitPattern = Pattern.compile("Outfit.*?:(.*?)Why:", Pattern.DOTALL);
Matcher outfitMatcher = outfitPattern.matcher(suggestions);

while (outfitMatcher.find()) {
    String itemsBlock = outfitMatcher.group(1);
    String[] items = itemsBlock.split("\n");

    List<String> cleanItems = new ArrayList<>();
    for (String item : items) {
        if (item.trim().startsWith("-")) {
            cleanItems.add(item.trim().substring(1).trim());
        }
    }
    results.add(cleanItems);
}
```

## Your Current Options in the Code

I've added 3 options to your `parseOutfits` method:

**OPTION 1 (Active):** Splits at each "Outfit" occurrence
```java
String[] blocks = suggestions.split("(?=Outfit\\s*\\d*:?)");
```

**OPTION 2 (Commented):** Extract content between START_WORD and END_WORD
```java
Pattern pattern = Pattern.compile("START_WORD(.*?)END_WORD");
Matcher matcher = pattern.matcher(suggestions);
while (matcher.find()) {
    results.add(matcher.group(1).trim());
}
```

**OPTION 3 (Commented):** Extract content from "Outfit:" to "Why:"
```java
String[] blocks = suggestions.split("(?=Outfit:)");
for (String block : blocks) {
    if (block.contains("Why:")) {
        String outfit = block.substring(0, block.indexOf("Why:")).trim();
        results.add(outfit);
    }
